Items completed and removed from this file:
- Configuration management (0.2.0 — lib/config.cpp, 3-tier system)
- Health checks (0.2.3 — healthcheck: spec section)
- Container dependencies (0.2.3 — depends: spec section)
- crate stack multi-container orchestration (0.2.3)
- Enhanced crate list with ports/mounts/healthcheck columns (0.2.3)
- CHANGELOG.md (0.2.0)
- Native FreeBSD API wrappers replacing shell commands (0.2.5)
- crate stop TARGET (0.3.0 — lifecycle.cpp)
- crate restart TARGET (0.3.0 — lifecycle.cpp)
- crate stats TARGET with JSON support (0.3.0 — lifecycle.cpp)
- crate logs TARGET with follow/tail (0.3.0 — lifecycle.cpp)
- Restart policy (on-failure/always/unless-stopped) with retry loop (0.3.15)
- Graceful shutdown with configurable timeout (0.3.0 — lifecycle.cpp)
- Per-container firewall policy with IPv4+IPv6 (0.3.0 — PfctlOps)
- Per-stack DNS via unbound (0.3.0 — stack.cpp)
- Inter-container network policies (0.3.0 — stack.cpp)
- IP pool allocator for stacks (0.3.0 — stack.cpp)
- RCTL I/O enforcement with verification (0.3.0 — run_jail.cpp)
- OOM detection and exit diagnostics (0.3.0 — run_jail.cpp)
- Per-container Prometheus metrics (0.3.0 — daemon/metrics.cpp)
- ZFS disk quotas per-container (0.3.0 — zfs_ops.cpp; runtime
  application bug fixed in 0.8.31)
- Base system caching with SHA256 (0.3.0 — create.cpp)
- CI: Linux unit tests, FreeBSD lite/full build, release binary workflow
- pkg/add support — install pre-built .txz files via `pkg add` (0.5.5)
- X11 shared-mode security warning at validate + run time (0.5.6)
- pkg/chroot output captured to /var/log/crate/create-<jail>.log (0.5.7)
- Symmetric encryption for .crate (AES-256-CBC + PBKDF2 via -P) (0.5.4)
- ed25519 signing for .crate (-K to sign, -V to verify; .sig sidecar) (0.5.8)
- Audit logging — JSONL append to /var/log/crate/audit.log (0.5.9;
  optional dual-write to syslog via cap_syslog added in 0.8.24)
- Cross-device file shares — single-file nullfs bind fallback when host
  and jail-side path are on different devices (0.6.0 — lib/share_pure.cpp)
- crated F2 write API (partial) — POST /restart, snapshot CRUD
  (GET/POST /snapshots, DELETE /snapshots/<name>), and SSE stats stream
  (GET /stats/stream) (0.6.1 — daemon/routes.cpp + routes_pure.cpp)
- crate top — live, htop-style resource monitor for all crate-managed
  jails: 1 Hz refresh, NAME/JID/IP/CPU%/MEM/DISK/PROC columns, alternate
  screen + 'q' to quit; non-tty stdout emits one frame and exits
  (0.6.2 — lib/top.cpp + lib/top_pure.cpp)
- Auto-create bridge — opt-in via `options.net.auto_create_bridge:
  true` in the spec; runtime creates the bridge if missing and
  destroys it on teardown only when crate created it
  (0.6.3 — lib/bridge_pure.cpp + lib/run.cpp)
- WebSocket console — RFC 6455-compliant WS endpoint for interactive
  shells in jails. Listens on a dedicated TCP/IPv6 socket
  (`console_ws_port` in crated.conf), Bearer-token authenticated,
  proxies bytes between the client and a jexec'd /bin/sh via PTY
  (0.6.4 — daemon/ws_pure.cpp + daemon/ws_console.cpp)
- crated export/import endpoints — POST /containers/<name>/export
  produces a .crate in /var/run/crate; GET /exports/<file> streams
  it back; POST /imports/<name> accepts a raw .crate body, sniffs
  xz/encrypted magic bytes, atomic-renames into place. F2 write API
  is now feature-complete (0.6.5 — daemon/transfer_pure.cpp +
  daemon/routes.cpp).
- SNMP AgentX wire protocol — full Get/GetNext PDU dispatcher
  replaces stub mode. Decoders for header (with little-endian flag
  honoured), OID, OctetString, SearchRange, GetRequest payload;
  VarBind encoders for Integer/Counter32/Counter64/Gauge32/
  TimeTicks/OctetString/OID/Null + END_OF_MIB_VIEW/NO_SUCH_OBJECT/
  NO_SUCH_INSTANCE exceptions. Fixed long-standing bug where OIDs
  were encoded with a 4-byte n_subid (RFC 2741 §5.1 mandates 1).
  (0.6.6 — snmpd/mib_pure.cpp + snmpd/mib.cpp dispatchOnce loop)
- Hub web dashboard — minimal vanilla-JS UI in hub/web/: cluster
  summary, node table, container table with start/stop/restart/
  destroy buttons (POST direct to per-node crated). Backed by new
  pure aggregator module + GET /api/v1/aggregate endpoint
  (0.6.7 — hub/aggregator_pure.cpp + hub/web/{index.html,app.js,style.css})
- Inter-container DNS — host-wide .crate zone. New `crate inter-dns`
  command rebuilds /etc/hosts (between crate-marker comments) and
  /usr/local/etc/unbound/conf.d/crate.conf from JailQuery state and
  triggers `unbound-control reload` (0.6.8 — lib/inter_dns_pure.cpp +
  lib/inter_dns.cpp)
- WireGuard config tooling — `crate vpn wireguard render-conf` reads
  a small YAML spec (interface + peers list) and emits a wg-quick(8)-
  compatible INI config. Validates 44-char base64 keys, IPv4/IPv6
  CIDRs (with prefix bounds), and bracketed-IPv6 / hostname endpoint
  forms before rendering. Runtime kernel-level integration is tracked
  separately (0.6.9 — lib/wireguard_pure.cpp + lib/vpn.cpp)
- IPsec config tooling — `crate vpn ipsec render-conf` reads a YAML
  spec (conns list with left/right endpoints + subnets + IKE/ESP
  proposals) and emits a strongSwan ipsec.conf-compatible config.
  Validates host (incl. dotted-numeric octet bounds), CIDR, proposal
  strings, keyexchange/authby/auto enums (0.6.10 — lib/ipsec_pure.cpp
  + lib/vpn.cpp)
- crate inspect TARGET — pretty-printed JSON snapshot of a running
  container's runtime state (identity, jail params, interfaces,
  mounts, RCTL counters, ZFS dataset/origin, GUI session). Stable
  key order so diffs across snapshots stay clean
  (0.6.11 — lib/inspect_pure.cpp + lib/inspect.cpp)
- Man pages for crated(8) and crate-hub(8) — mdoc-format pages that
  match the existing crate.5 style: NAME / SYNOPSIS / DESCRIPTION /
  ENDPOINTS / AUTHENTICATION / CONFIGURATION / FILES / CAVEATS /
  SEE ALSO / HISTORY / AUTHORS sections. Installed via the existing
  `make install-daemon` target (which now ships crated.8.gz too) and
  a new `make install-hub-man` target (0.6.12 — crated.8 +
  crate-hub.8)
- WireGuard runtime — `options.wireguard.config: <path>` in the
  spec runs `wg-quick up <path>` before the jail starts and
  registers a RunAtEnd handler for `wg-quick down <path>` on
  teardown. Path validated against shell metacharacters and `..`
  segments (0.6.13 — lib/wireguard_runtime_pure.cpp + lib/run.cpp).
  Full kernel-level integration without delegating to wg-quick
  remains a future item.
- Container migration — `crate migrate <name> --from <ep> --to <ep>
  --from-token-file <f> --to-token-file <f>` orchestrates a 5-step
  move via the F2 API: export-on-source, download to /tmp,
  upload-to-dest, start-on-dest, then stop-on-source. Source
  container is stopped only AFTER the destination reports start
  success. Tokens come from chmod-600 files so they don't appear
  in `ps`. Endpoints validated for IPv4/IPv6/hostname forms; names
  validated for shell-safety (0.6.14 — lib/migrate_pure.cpp +
  lib/migrate.cpp + curl(1) for HTTP).
- Datacenter grouping in hub — NodeConfig/NodeStatus gain a
  `datacenter:` field; new GET /api/v1/datacenters endpoint returns
  per-DC summary (nodes total/reachable/down + containers total).
  Web dashboard shows a Datacenters table above the Nodes table.
  Empty datacenter is canonicalised to "default". Admin UI for
  editing DCs is left for later (0.6.15 — hub/datacenter_pure.cpp
  + hub/api.cpp + hub/web/{index.html,app.js})
- crate backup / crate restore — ZFS-send-based snapshot streams
  (0.7.0 — lib/backup_pure.cpp + lib/backup.cpp). Native libzfs
  recv path added in 0.8.29.
- API tokens with TTL + scope — crated.conf tokens gain optional
  `expires_at:` (UTC ISO 8601) and `scope:` (list of path globs)
  (0.7.1 — lib/auth_pure.cpp + daemon/auth.cpp).
- crate replicate — ZFS storage replication via ssh
  (0.7.2 — lib/replicate_pure.cpp + lib/replicate.cpp).
- HA failover policy in hub (0.7.3 — hub/ha_pure.cpp + hub/api.cpp +
  hub/poller.cpp).
- Resource pools + ACL — tokens in crated.conf gain optional
  `pools:` whitelist (0.7.4 — lib/pool_pure.cpp + daemon/auth.cpp).
- ZFS warm-template caching (0.7.5 — lib/warm_pure.cpp + lib/warm.cpp).
- crate retune — live RCTL adjustment for a running jail
  (0.7.6 — lib/retune_pure.cpp + lib/retune.cpp).
- crate throttle — TRUE token-bucket network rate limiting via
  dummynet(4) accessed through ipfw(8) (0.7.7 — lib/throttle_pure.cpp
  + lib/throttle.cpp).
- `network: auto` — zero-config networking shorthand for vnet jails
  (0.8.17 top-level, 0.7.18 nested form). Expands into bridge +
  auto-create-bridge + auto-IP + auto-SNAT/rdr.
- `gui: auto` — zero-config GUI mode for desktop-app jails. Single
  spec line covers X11 cookie copy + /tmp/.X11-unix bind +
  /dev/dri/* devfs unhide + Wayland socket bind (assembled across
  0.7.19 / 0.8.11 / 0.8.18).
- `crate vm-wrap` — bhyve jailer renderer (0.8.16; see TODO2 B).
- IPv6 NPTv6 Phase 2 — `network_pool6:` config field actually
  configures jail-side v6 (0.8.20). NAT66/NPTv6 pf rules tracked
  separately for a future release.
- Spec registry + control-plane PostStart (0.8.21).
- 0.8.21 dead-code audit closure — see CHANGELOG entries for 0.8.22
  through 0.8.37.
